      "role": "user",
      "content": "makes sense. so if i have my COGS and my average inventory, i can get the ratio. but i'm also trying to present this to my boss to explain why the numbers look so weird this quarter. besides the math, what are some common operational reasons for such a sudden spike in shrinkage? like, what should we be looking for in the warehouse to figure out where the leaks are happening?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A sudden spike in shrinkage usually points to a systemic issue, not just random loss. You should start by reviewing security footage and access logs for areas where high-value electronics are stored. Common operational causes include inadequate cycle counting procedures, poor internal controls over high-risk items, or potential employee misconduct. Examining receiving and shipping docks is also crucial, as these are prime areas for theft or misplacement.",
      "source": "target",
